title: Determining The Most Difficult Major at UCSD
description: This project set out to investigate a commonly held belief among college students: that STEM majors are objectively more difficult and time-consuming than humanities majors. Using the CAPEs dataset, a collection of student-reported experiences with UCSD courses, we attempted to quantify the demands of various departments across key metrics like study hours, grades and professor recommendations. In doing so, our analysis not only confirmed some long standing assumptions but also challenged others, offering a more nuanced picture of academic difficulty at UCSD.

title: Analyzing Recipe Calories vs Ratings
description: This data science project, conducted at UCSD for the DSC80: Practice and Application of Data Science Course, focuses on exploring factors that can and do contribute to a recipe's average rating.

title: Natural Disaster Project
description: Used ERA5 data to study weather patterns that were correlated with storms in the Southeastern United States.
